      "content": "The argument for a limit is compelling, as allowing exemptions from civil rights laws could indeed jeopardize the foundational principles of equality under the law. The legal challenge often centers on whether the religious claim overrides fundamental state interests, such as public safety or non-discrimination. Therefore, most modern legal frameworks attempt to draw a line where religious freedom cannot infringe upon constitutionally protected rights of others.",
      "source": "target",
