      "content": "It is not about one right always defeating the other, but about how the courts weigh competing fundamental rights. The concept of conscience protection is a core tenet of many democracies, just as public order is. The legal system attempts to find a narrow path where necessary mandates can be enforced while still respecting sincere religious objections where possible. This balancing act is what makes the legal landscape over this issue so difficult.",
